  "text": "Chemical analyses of milk samples were performed using validated micro-methods, which required less than 1.5 mL of sample volume. The methods were based on a modified ether Mojonnier extraction (1.0 mL) for fat, elemental analysis (260 μL) for protein, and UPLC-MS/MS (100 μL) for lactose with corresponding CV's of 1.7, 1.8, and 2.3% respectively. These micro-methods were recently published [CITATION_1] .",
